articles.title: Stephanie Ruhle 'sick and scared' after COVID diagnosis
articles.description: MSNBC anchor Stephanie Ruhle revealed Monday that she and her family are recovering from coronavirus after she spent the better part of the past two weeks in bed. The mother of three, who is in quarantine at her New Jersey home, told viewers that she was “incredibly lucky” that her symptoms felt “just like a terrible flu” and that she was able to take time off from work to focus on her health.
